caption: I am not one to complain, but I received the absolute worst customer service I have ever seen here- will never be back here, will never recommend that anyone go here, and will most certainly never spend a dime here ever.
Decent

Very good pizza by the slice with many different toppings from just about anything a person could think of. Creativity with pizza at a good price as well.

I was a loyal customer and avid fan of Mesa my whole 4 years at the University of Iowa. This changed when they kicked me out when it was -5 degrees and -25 windchill. I went in and pulled my mask down momentarily to clarify my order in which I was told I had a warning. They had two tables set up in which our group set up and prepared to eat. I removed my mask to eat and I was kicked out as I was then told those tables are for standing. I have never been removed from a business or bar. I talked with security (who were very respectful and genuine) and they told our group to wait near the door for our Uber and we agreed with no problem. The manager then came over and I apologized for the misunderstanding and pleaded with him to wait inside to avoid the weather in which he said "the weather is not my problem and get out of my restaurant, I don't care if it's dangerous". He had the biggest ego I have ever seen and was extremely aggressive and rude. I've never been so turned off by management and treated with that level of disrespect. I truly regret the last 4 years of business. I urge you to not make the same mistake as me. Choose to give your dollar to businesses who treat others well. There are plenty in Iowa City and I've never had another bad experience. Some businesses that stick out nearby include Mickeys (Bar Food), Estelas (Mexican Food), and Falbo Bros (Pizza). I would encourage you to vote with your dollar and go to one of those instead.

I no longer live in Iowa as I went to messa when I was a student at the university of Iowa. Thinking back to my college days I think about how absolutely amazing messa pizza is and how much I went there. I highly recommend the Mac n cheese pizza. I have such a taste for it I’m tempted to get in my car and drive 2.5 hours to get a slice of pizza. Go try this place and you will go there every single week!
Good Pizza

An Iowa city staple. The speciality pizza’s are so good. You can order any slice and be satisfied with your choices. Cheap slices, delicious taste.
Awesome buffalo chicken pizza. Perfectly crispy crust.with delicious tasty toppings. Skip the garlic bread. It tasted like like frozen bread sticks that were warmed up in a microwave.

They even have 1 side of the counter for vegetarian slices and 1 side of the counter for slices with meat. Ya know, I've heard very divisive opinions about Mesa Pizza here and I acknowledge that their crust is only fine (better than Pagliais), and not as good as The Wedge's or Maggie's's. What Mesa brings to the playing field though is fresh toppings in creative and varied combinations, as well as a cheap 2 slice afternoon lunch deal. If you consider this with the fact that it's right downtown and that there's never a long wait, you got yourself a leading competitor in the Iowa City pizza game.

If big slices and variety are your thing, this is the place to be. Be it will or destiny, their pizza is always hot and crispy. When I'm craving some variety, my personal favorite are the Buffalo Chicken, Philly Steak, and Pad Thai slices. However, it's hard to resist their pepperoni and salami, which features paper thin slices of delicious soppressata drizzle with *just* the right amount of balsamic. My only complaint is their prices - two slices and a drink can approach $10. The lunch special should be available around the clock in a town like Iowa City as well - there are plenty of grad students who would come in for the special if it were offered later in the day! But, I understand this is a Big Ten College town, and not everything is cheap! To conclude, if you're wanting a more east-coast type of slice, or perhaps something a little more unique, Mesa can't be beat. It is delicious.

I really enjoyed the pizza for years. I’ve politely asked to have chicken added to their avocado delight for carry out twice, once a year ago and once just a moment ago. Both times I was told they don’t do custom modifications no exceptions. They have even offered this by the slice before, but since it’s not on the menu I can never have it again. We were appalled at the service. I pointed to the different slices asking what kind they were. (There was about fifteen different varieties) explaining we have never been there before. After I asked about 3 different slices,  the girl behind the counter said, "I'm not going to tell you what every different kind is." .... I was lost for words. I wouldn't rate this establishment a 1 star. Still waiting for the manager to call and explain why their employee was so rude. We left and went to the Wedge where without even asking, described every type of pizza. Thank you guys from the Wedge for saving the day.

Awesome variety by the slice

Mesa pizza-overpriced, kinda icky, and misleading menu.  I ordered a vegan 14" and a 20" chicken pineapple barbeque sauce delivered through orderup.  The bill was 52.00 with a 15% tip.  The vegan was good, but certainly not THAT good for the price ($18) The sauce is tasteless and quite sugary.  The chicken barbeque was totally inedible.  It consisted of crust slathered in bbq with very little chicken and pineapple AND NO CHEESE.   I was (and am) flummoxed by this.  When I called to complain, I was beligerently informed that it usually doesn't come with cheese. Yes, I was put off and slightly peeved, but hello?  Who orders (a non vegan) pizza and has to SPECIFY cheese?  And who charges $27 for a "pizza" that has a topping value at roughly $2?  Maybe two pieces were choked down, and the rest sits wasted on the countertop.  The person taking my complaint deigned to offer me a free 12" pizza.  All I had to do was give my name and pick up my pizza next time.  I would expect that the free pizza wouldn't be any better, nor would I trust it not to contain foreign matter, as the customer service on the phone consisted of "I WAS going to tell you I would give you a free pizza."  It would be nice to get an admission that the menu might be misleading if cheese is not a default ingredient on a PIZZA.  A non-vegan pizza.  Trust: order from The Wedge.  It's a much better pizza and a much better value.

Pizza types are interesting.  Wish they would tell me which pizzas are fresh though, because heating up an old pizza just doesn't taste as good.  Also, staff don't really seem to know which pizzas are which. You just have to see if the pizza has the toppings you want.  But at 1am, no one is complaining.

Pizza was good and artwork on walls is cool. I had the mac n cheese pizza and enjoyed it a lot. Only thing is the atmosphere is a little grungy but pretty great pizza even if it's in a dive.

(Lunchtime experience) Maybe this pizza is solely intended to be consumed while drunk, because it's just bad during the day.  The crust lacks any color, a sign of undercooking and no brushed oil.  It sits out without heat application so the cheese gets re-hardened. The cashier isn't in the mood to let it re-heat long enough in the oven -- end result: lukewarm pizza.  The selection of toppings is one of two extremes: boring or over-the-top strange.  I'm guessing this was good pizza some many years ago, but the sheep just keep repeating "awesome pizza!" generation after generation without thinking for themselves.
AMAZING LATE NIGHT FOOD!! Love the buffalo chicken pizza!
